rev 3504:  xela | 2002-10-26 04:31:24 -0400 (Sat, 26 Oct 2002) | 19 lines

Encapsulated subversion pools in the new class Pool.

* src/Makefile.in
* src/svncpp/pool.h
* src/svncpp/pool.cpp

Debugged memory hole in Client::status and Client::singleStatus.
The reason were allocations in the global pool instead of a
local sub-pool. Resolved through introduction of the new Pool class.

* src/svncpp/client.cpp (Client::status, Client::singleStatus)

Removed the remark "This class is never directly used" from the
Client class description, since it is directly used since the
introduction of the Methode status and singleStatus.

* src/svncpp/client.h


