rev 3097:  bmatzelle | 2002-08-29 12:43:23 -0400 (Thu, 29 Aug 2002) | 65 lines


* src/svncpp/exception.h
  Includes two exception handling classes: Exception, a base exception class, 
  and ClientException, a Subversion client exception handling class.  

* src/svncpp/exception.cpp
  Same as the header.

* doc/svncpp.dox
  Now when CHM documentation is created the file is svncpp.chm.

The following files had the svncpp modify include moved from the header 
file to the source file because it was causing compile errors with the 
basic_string include in exception.h.
* src/commit_action.h
* src/commit_action.cpp
* src/copy_action.cpp
* src/copy_action.h
* src/delete_action.cpp
* src/delete_action.h
* src/import_action.cpp
* src/import_action.h
* src/mkdir_action.cpp
* src/mkdir_action.h

* src/auth_baton.cpp
  Added the store_auth_info and got_new_auth_info according to the updated
  Subversion API.

* src/svncpp/auth.h
  Eliminated the include of the deprecated error.h header.

* src/svncpp/auth.cpp
  Added the store_auth_info and got_new_auth_info according to the updated
  Subversion API.

* src/svncpp/client.h
  Eliminated the getError() method because the Error class is deprecated.
  
* src/svncpp/client.cpp
  Same as header.

In the following files all methods now have exception handling added to them 
and all returns were changed from bool to void accordingly.
* src/svncpp/modify.cpp
* src/svncpp/modify.h
* src/svncpp/property.cpp
* src/svncpp/property.h
* src/svncpp/status.cpp
* src/svncpp/status.h

* src/svncpp/error.h
  Removed because it has been replaced by the Exception classes.

* src/svncpp/error.cpp
  Same as header file.

* src/svncpp/svncpp.dsp
  Add the exception.* files and removed the error.* files.  Also switched 
  the run-time library in all builds to multi-threaded DLL.

* src/tests/svncpp/svncpp.cpp
  Altered all tests to utilize exception handling (try,catch).


